Package: castSDM
Type: Package
Title: Causal Structure-Informed Species Distribution Modeling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Liqiang", "",
      email = "2759831686@qq.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-6966-4633")
    )
  )
Description: Integrates causal inference methods with species distribution
    modeling. Learns species-specific causal structures via Directed Acyclic
    Graphs (DAG), estimates Average Treatment Effects (ATE) using Double
    Machine Learning, and builds Causally-Informed Multi-Layer Perceptrons
    (CI-MLP) for habitat suitability prediction. Supports comparison with
    traditional SDM methods including Random Forest, MaxEnt, and Boosted
    Regression Trees. Provides spatially heterogeneous Conditional Average
    Treatment Effect (CATE) estimation via causal forests.
